    "content": "Buying property in Bangalore requires rigorous legal due diligence. A single missing document can lead to decades of litigation. Based on our 35 years of experience at Vani Estates, here is the ultimate document verification checklist for 2026.\n\n**1. The Mother Deed & Sale Deed**\nThe Mother Deed traces the absolute origin of the property. You must ensure the chain of title is unbroken. The current Sale Deed must be registered at the Sub-Registrar's office, confirming the seller holds undisputed ownership.\n\n**2. 30-Year Encumbrance Certificate (EC)**\nAn EC (Form 15) proves that the property is free from legal dues, mortgages, or pending loans. Always demand an EC covering at least the last 30 years to be absolutely safe.\n\n**3. Approved Building Plan & Layout Approvals**\nFor apartments or independent houses, verify that the building plan was approved by the BBMP or BDA. Any deviation from this plan can result in the property being classified as illegal, cutting off your access to standard bank loans.\n\n**4. Occupancy Certificate (OC) & Completion Certificate (CC)**\nAn OC is issued by the municipal corporation only after a building is constructed according to the approved plan. Without an OC, securing an A-Khata, a water connection, or a resale buyer later will be nearly impossible.\n\n*Document verification is not a DIY project. The Vani Estates legal team meticulously audits every property before we list it. Let our experts protect your investment.*",
