    "excerpt": "Both are popular with IT professionals, but the right choice depends on your lifestyle, budget, and commute. Here's a head-to-head comparison.",
    "content": "Whitefield and JP Nagar are two of Bangalore's most popular destinations for IT professionals — but they're vastly different in character, pricing, and investment potential. Let's compare.\n\n**Pricing (2026)**\n- Whitefield: ₹6,500-9,500 per sq ft for resale, ₹8,000-12,000 for new projects\n- JP Nagar: ₹8,500-14,000 per sq ft for resale, ₹12,000-18,000 for new projects\n\n**Commute**\n- Whitefield: Direct access to ITPL, EPIP, RMZ Ecoworld. Metro now connects to Whitefield. Average commute to office: 10-30 minutes.\n- JP Nagar: 30-60 minutes to Whitefield/ORR via Metro+road. Better for Manyata or Electronic City professionals (20-30 mins).\n\n**Lifestyle & Amenities**\nWhitefield is purpose-built for IT lifestyle — Phoenix Marketcity, Forum Shantiniketan, international schools, modern restaurants. JP Nagar offers a more traditional South Bangalore vibe — local markets, established schools, family-oriented community.\n\n**Investment Potential**\n- Whitefield: Higher rental yields (3.5-4.5%), driven by IT tenant demand\n- JP Nagar: Better capital appreciation (28-35% over 5 years), driven by limited land supply\n\n**The Verdict**\nIf you work in Whitefield/ORR and want modern amenities + rental income: Buy in Whitefield. If you work in Electronic City/Bannerghatta or want long-term wealth creation: JP Nagar wins.\n\n**Sample Listings**\nVani Estates currently has properties in both areas — [Sohum Isiri 2 BHK in Whitefield](/?property=9) at ₹90 Lakh, and [Maratt Pimento 4 BHK in JP Nagar](/?property=6) at ₹7.5 Crore. Visit our listings page to compare.",
