    "id": 32,
    "title": "Rental Yield Comparison — Best Areas to Buy for Rental Income in South Bangalore 2026",
    "date": "May 8, 2026",
    "category": "Investment Guide",
    "excerpt": "If your goal is monthly rental income, not all South Bangalore localities are equal. Here are the top areas ranked by rental yield in 2026.",
    "content": "For investors looking at South Bangalore for rental income, choosing the right locality is critical. Rental yields here range from 2% (low-yield, high-appreciation) to 4.5% (high-yield, moderate-appreciation). Here's the 2026 ranking.\n\n**Tier 1: Highest Yield (3.5-4.5%)**\n\n**JP Nagar (Phases 6-8)**: 3.8-4.2% yield. High demand from IT professionals working at Bannerghatta Road tech parks. 2 BHK at ₹1 Cr rents for ₹35-40k.\n\n**BTM Layout**: 4.0-4.5% yield. Maximum demand due to proximity to Koramangala startups. 2 BHK at ₹85 Lakh rents for ₹30-35k.\n\n**Bommanahalli & Begur**: 4.2-4.5% yield. Lower entry price but high IT tenant demand. ₹65 Lakh apartments rent for ₹22-25k.\n\n**Tier 2: Balanced (2.8-3.5%)**\n\n**JP Nagar (Phases 1-5)**: 3.0-3.5% yield. Established locality with mix of IT and family tenants. Rental of ₹40-50k for ₹1.4 Cr properties.\n\n**Banashankari (Stages 2-3)**: 2.8-3.2% yield. Family-heavy tenant base, longer lease durations.\n\n**Tier 3: Capital Growth Focus (2.0-2.8%)**\n\n**Jayanagar**: 2.0-2.5% yield BUT 30-40% capital appreciation in 5 years. ₹1.2 Cr property rents for only ₹25-28k. The math: you make more on appreciation than rent here.\n\n**Basavanagudi**: 2.2-2.8% yield. Heritage area, slow rental growth but stable.\n\n**Best Strategy by Investor Type**\n\n**For Salaried Professionals Wanting Passive Income**: Invest in JP Nagar Phases 6-8 or BTM Layout. Use rental to offset EMI. Sweet spot: ₹85 Lakh - 1.2 Cr properties.\n\n**For HNIs Seeking Wealth Creation**: Invest in Jayanagar. Lower yield but you'll make ₹40-60 Lakh on appreciation in 5 years on a ₹1.5 Cr property.\n\n**For Senior Citizens Wanting Stable Income**: Banashankari or JP Nagar Phases 1-5. Family tenants, longer leases, predictable income.\n\n**Tax Considerations**\nDon't forget — rental income is taxed at your slab rate after 30% standard deduction and home loan interest deduction. A ₹40,000/month rental nets approximately ₹25,000 after tax for someone in 30% bracket.\n\nVani Estates manages rental portfolios for 50+ NRIs and out-of-city investors. We handle tenant screening, rent collection, and maintenance — so your investment truly is passive. Call us to discuss.",
    "slug": "rental-yield-comparison-best-areas-to-buy-for-rental-income-in-south-bangalore-2026"
